main event: An unidentified flying object was observed near Seattle and Renton, Washington on 13 May 1953.
interesting points: The object was described as round and the size of a marble., One observer estimated the altitude to be between 20,000 to 35,000 feet., The sighting lasted approximately 2-3 minutes., The object displayed erratic behavior, oscillating or bobbing up and down., No sound was heard from the object and there was no observed propulsion system.
sighted object: one round object resembling the size of a marble
witness description: Mr. (entire name blanked out), observed through a four power telescope
